<gxl xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
	<graph id="Drosophila_Cell_Cycle_Variants" class="regulatory" nodeorder="CycD Rb E2F CycE CycA Rux Fzy Fzr CycB Wee1 Stg Notch Dap Ago">
<node id="CycD" name="CycD/cdc" maxvalue="1">
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="http://flybase.org/reports/FBgn0010315.html"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.sdbonline.org/fly/newgene/cyclind.htm"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment>G1 cyclin. 
Heterodimarizes with Cdc kinase. </comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="50" y="150" width="50" height="20" backgroundColor="#ccffff" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Rb" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rux:Rb" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rux:Rb CycA:Rb" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycB:Rb Rux:Rb" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycB:Rb Rux:Rb CycA:Rb" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="!CycD &amp; !CycE &amp; ((!CycA &amp; !CycB) | Rux)"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12881421"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://flybase.org/reports/FBgn0015799.html"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.sdbonline.org/fly/newgene/retnbls1.htm"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q24472"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment>Transcription factor that negatively regulates members of the E2F family, thereby preventing entrance into mitosis.
Rb binds to E2F and thereby inactivates it.
Inactivation of Rb at the G1-S transition promotes entry into S phase.
[Weng et al (2003) EMBO J 22(15): 3865-75]</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="146" y="143" width="50" height="20" backgroundColor="#ffffff" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Rux" name="Roughex" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rux:Rux" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rux:Rux CycA:Rux" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycB:Rux Rux:Rux" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycE:Rux" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycE:Rux Rux:Rux" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycE:Rux Rux:Rux CycA:Rux" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycE:Rux CycB:Rux Rux:Rux" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycD:Rux" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycD:Rux Rux:Rux" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycD:Rux Rux:Rux CycA:Rux" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycD:Rux CycB:Rux Rux:Rux" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="!(CycD &amp; CycE) &amp; (!(CycA | CycB) | Rux) &amp; !(CycA &amp; CycB)"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10607563"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11231149"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://flybase.org/reports/FBgn0003302.html"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.sdbonline.org/fly/newgene/roughex1.htm"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P50445"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment>Rux is involved in the regulation of G1. 
Mutations in Rux cause cells to circumvent G1 and all cells enter S phase
Acts through Cyclin A during premiotic G2 to regulate meiosis. 
Also a negative regulator of G1 in the developing eye. 
Rux inhibits Cdk1-cyclin A kinase activity during metaphase, thereby contributing to exit from mitosis. 
[Foley et al. (1999) Curr Biol 9(23):1392-402]
[Foley &amp; Sprenger (2001) Curr Biol 11(3):151-60]</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="20" y="220" width="50" height="20" backgroundColor="#ffff33" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Wee1" name="Wee1" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rux:Wee1" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycB:Wee1 Rux:Wee1" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="!CycB | Rux"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/8573790"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://flybase.org/reports/FBgn0011737.html"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.sdbonline.org/fly/newgene/weekin1.htm"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P54350"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment>Protein kinase targetting Cdc2, thereby preventing premature activation of the mitotic program. 
Drosophila Wee1 kinase rescues fission yeast from mitotic catastrophe and phosphorylates Drosophila Cdc2 in vitro. 
[Campbell et al (1995) Mol Biol Cell 6(10):1333-47]
</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="63" y="288" width="50" height="20" backgroundColor="#ff9999" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Fzy" name="Fizzy" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycB:Fzy" val="1"/>
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="http://flybase.org/reports/FBgn0001086.html"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.sdbonline.org/fly/newgene/fizzy1.htm"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment>Required for the acrivity of APC in mitosis. 
Functions to target the mitotic cyclins A and B for destruction in the egg and drive anaphase progression during meiosis. </comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="132" y="347" width="50" height="20" backgroundColor="#ff9933" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="CycA" name="CycA/cdc2" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" E2F:CycA" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="E2F &amp; !Rb &amp; !Fzr &amp; !Fzy"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="http://flybase.org/reports/FBgn0000404.html"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.sdbonline.org/fly/newgene/cyclina1.htm"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P14785"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment>CycA is a G2 Cyclin. 
Peaks in Prophase, then declines. 
Heterodimarizes with Cdc kinase. 
Degradation of CycA required for entry in mitosis. </comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="230" y="165" width="58" height="20" backgroundColor="#99ff00" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="CycE" name="CycE/cdc2c" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" E2F:CycE" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" E2F:CycE Ago:CycE" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" E2F:CycE Dap:CycE" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="E2F &amp; !Rb &amp; !(Ago &amp; Dap)"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="http://flybase.org/reports/FBgn0010382.html"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.sdbonline.org/fly/newgene/cyclin-e.htm"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P54733"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment>CycE induces S phase. 
Stable G1 quiescence requires the down-regulation of CycE. </comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="123" y="80" width="50" height="20" backgroundColor="#33ffcc" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="E2F" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rux:E2F" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rux:E2F CycA:E2F" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycB:E2F Rux:E2F" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycB:E2F Rux:E2F CycA:E2F" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="(!(CycA | CycB) | Rux) &amp; !Rb"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12881421"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://flybase.org/reports/FBgn0011766.html"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.sdbonline.org/fly/newgene/e2f.htm"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q27368"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment>E2F factors regulate the genes involved into S phase. 
Responsible for activation of S phase genes. 
[Weng et al (2003) EMBO J 22(15): 3865-75]</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="96" y="188" width="50" height="20" backgroundColor="#00ffff" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Fzr" name="Fizzy related" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rux:Fzr" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rux:Fzr CycA:Fzr" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycB:Fzr Rux:Fzr" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycB:Fzr Rux:Fzr CycA:Fzr" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Notch:Fzr" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Notch:Fzr Rux:Fzr" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Notch:Fzr Rux:Fzr CycA:Fzr" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Notch:Fzr CycB:Fzr Rux:Fzr" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Notch:Fzr CycB:Fzr Rux:Fzr CycA:Fzr" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Notch:Fzr CycE:Fzr" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Notch:Fzr CycE:Fzr Rux:Fzr" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Notch:Fzr CycE:Fzr Rux:Fzr CycA:Fzr" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Notch:Fzr CycE:Fzr CycB:Fzr Rux:Fzr" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Notch:Fzr CycE:Fzr CycB:Fzr Rux:Fzr CycA:Fzr" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="(!CycE | Notch) &amp; ((!CycA &amp; !CycB) | Rux)"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15062106"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18321983"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://flybase.org/reports/FBgn0003200.html"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.sdbonline.org/fly/newgene/fizyrel1.htm"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9288747"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment>Fzr (synonym: rap) negatively regulates the levels of cyclins A and B, thus promoting mitosis. 
Notch-Dependent Fizzy-Related expression Is required for the mitotic-to-endocycle transition in drosophila follicle cells.  
[Schaeffer et al (2004) Curr Biol 14(7):630-6]
APC/CFzr/Cdh1 promotes cell cycle progression during the Drosophila endocycle. 
[Narbonne-Reveau et al (2008) Development 135(8):1451-61]



Maternally derived fzr transcripts present at the onset of embryogenesis (Figure 2A) disappeared during the syncytial embryonic cycles (Figure 2B). Zygotic expression started in yolk nuclei after the thirteenth embryonic mitosis (during the stages where the nuclei at the egg periphery are cellularized) and was detectable during gastrulation (Figure 2C). In the newly formed cells at the egg periphery, we failed to detect signals above background during the stages of the embryonic division cycles 14 and 15 (Figure 2C, and data not shown). At stage 11, expression was observed in the salivary placodes and in the anterior and posterior midgut primordia at high levels (Figure 2D) followed by expression at lower levels apparently throughout the embryo (Figure 2F).
Fzr negatively regulates cyclins A, B and B3.
Loss of Fzr results in an extra cell cycle after mitosis 16 instead of G1 arrest in embryonic epidermis cell.
Overexpression of Fzr arrests mitosis 16 in G2.
Fzr is required for entry into endoreduplication in the salivary gland.
Overexpression of Fzr transform mitotic cycles into endocycles in imaginal disc cells.
CycE inhibits Fzr.
[Sigrist &amp; Lehner (1997) Cell 90(4)671-81]</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="199" y="303" width="50" height="20" backgroundColor="#ff0000" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Dap" name="CKI/Dap" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycE:Dap" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Notch:Dap CycE:Dap" val="1"/>
  <parameter val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="CycE | !Notch"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15576927"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://flybase.org/reports/FBgn0010316.html"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.sdbonline.org/fly/newgene/dacapo1.htm"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment>Cyclin dependent kinase inhibitor of the Cip/kip family. 
Dap levels oscillate in nurse cells along endocycles. 
Dap expression requires Cyclin E function. 
[Swanhart et al (2005)  Meth Mol Biol 296: 69-94]</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="278" y="80" width="50" height="20" backgroundColor="#ffff33" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Notch" name="Notch" maxvalue="1">
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15175253"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15062106"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://flybase.org/reports/FBgn0004647.html"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.sdbonline.org/fly/neural/notch1.htm"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P07207"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment>Notch executes the mitotic-to-endocycle switch by repressing String (blocking of M-phase), activating Fzr (allowing G1 progression) and repressing Dacapo (entry in S-phase). 
[Scherbata et al (2004) Development 131: 3169-81]
Notch-Dependent Fizzy-Related expression Is required for the mitotic-to-endocycle transition in drosophila follicle cells. 
[Schaeffer et al (2004) Curr Biol 14: 630-6]</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="298" y="165" width="50" height="20" backgroundColor="#ffffff" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Stg" name="String" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" E2F:Stg" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" E2F:Stg Rux:Stg" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" E2F:Stg CycB:Stg" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" E2F:Stg CycB:Stg Rux:Stg" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycB:Stg" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" CycB:Stg Rb:Stg" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" E2F:Stg CycB:Stg Rb:Stg" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="((E2F &amp; !Rb) | (CycB &amp; !Rux)) &amp; !Notch"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="http://flybase.org/reports/FBgn0003525.html"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.sdbonline.org/fly/newgene/string1.htm"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P20483"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment>Phosphatase ativator of CycB/cdc2 kinase. </comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="282" y="251" width="50" height="20" backgroundColor="#ff99ff" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="CycB" name="CycB/cdc2" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Stg:CycB" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Wee1:CycB Stg:CycB" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="(!Wee1 | Stg) &amp; !Fzy &amp; !Fzr"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="http://flybase.org/reports/FBgn0000405.html"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.sdbonline.org/fly/newgene/cyclinb1.htm"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P20439"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment>Cyc B is a G2 Cyclin. 
Peaks in prophase until metaphase. 
Heterodimarizes with Cdc kinase. 
Degradation of CycB required for completion of mitosis. </comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="138" y="252" width="58" height="20" backgroundColor="#00ff33" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Ago" name="Ago" maxvalue="1">
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="http://flybase.org/reports/FBgn0041171.html"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.sdbonline.org/fly/sturtevant/archipelago1.htm"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q9VZF4"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment> F box component of an SCF-ubiquitin ligase targeting cyclinE. 
Antagonizes dMyc activity. </comment>
  </annotation>

