<annotation>
  <linklist>
    <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15576927"/>
    <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15175253"/>
    <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15062106"/>
    <link xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11146648"/>
  </linklist>
  <comment>Model accounting for the control of three different variants of cell cycle in Drosophila: early embryonic syncytial cell cycles, endocycles (in larva and chorion cells), and canonical cell cycles (e.g. in imaginal discs).
Syncytial cycles: oscillations of CycA/B complexes, Wee1, Fzy and Stg
Endocycles: oscillations CycE/Cdc2c and repression of CycA andt CycB dependent activities 
Pending question: is CycD activity required for endocycles?

General references:
[Swanhart et al (2005)  Meth Mol Biol 296: 69-94]
[Shcherbata et al (2004) Development 131: 3169-81]
[Schaeffer et al (2004) Curr Biol 14: 630-6]
[Vidwans &amp; Su (2001) Nat Cell Biol 3(1): E35-9]

</comment>
</annotation>
	</graph>
</gxl>
